[SN]TITLE[SN]
European Championships: Walker clinches quarter-final spot

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Kurt Walker is just one win away from a European Championships medal after a split-decision victory over number two seed Tayfur Aliyev in Ukraine.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Lisburn bantamweight edged the contest against his opponent from Azerbaijan to secure a place in the quarter-finals.
Walker will now take on Italian Raffaele Di Serio on Wednesday.
Belfast pair Sean McComb and Brendan Irvine have also progressed to the quarter-finals.
The last 16 victories secure a place at August's World Championships for the three local boxers.
Holy Trinity fighter McComb stunned world number one Vitaly Dunaytsev with a 3-2 majority win against the World and European light-welterweight title holder.
McComb faces England's Luke McCormack in a last-eight bout.
Rio Olympian Irvine beat Turkish opponent Bathuhan Citfci on a unanimous 5-0 decision to advance.
The flyweight goes up against Gabriel Escobar of Spain in the quarter-finals on Wednesday.
